s.be/en/michaelina Exhibition website] by [[Museum aan de Stroom]]\n*''Michaelina Wautier (1614-1689)'', catalog and 2018 art exhibition in Antwerp, by Katlijne Van der Stighelen, 2018. [https://www.mas.be/sites/mas/files/MAS_Michaelina_gids_EN.pdf Handbook for exhibition]\n* [https://rkd.nl/explore/artists/85684 RKD record] for Michaelina Wautier\n* BALat record for Michaelina Wautier in [[Royal Institute for Cultural Heritage]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Michaelina Wautier|state=expanded}}\n{{Lists of paintings}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of paintings|Wautier]]\n[[Category:Paintings by Michaelina Wautier| ]]\n", "name_user": "Ham II", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_paintings_by_Michaelina_Wautier"}
{"title_page": "Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf, BWV 226", "text_new": "{{short description|Motet by Johann Sebastian Bach}}\n{{Infobox Bach composition\n| title                 = {{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}\n| bwv                   = 226\n| type                  = [[Motet (Bach)|Motet]]\n| image                 = Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf.JPEG\n| image_upright         = 1.2\n| caption               = Manuscript\n| key                   = [[B-flat major]]\n| occasion              = Funeral of [[Johann Heinrich Ernesti]]\n| performed             = {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|1729|10|21|df=y}}|location=[[Paulinerkirche, Leipzig]]}}\n| bible                 = {{Sourcetext|source=Bible|version=King James|book=Romans|chapter=8|verse=26|range=\u201327}}\n| chorale               = [[Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott]]\n| movements             = 3\n| vocal                 = 2 choirs [[SATB|{{abbr|SATB|soprano, alto, tenor and bass}}]]\n| instrumental          = strings with choir I, woodwinds with choir II, continuo\n| italic title          = no\n}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', BWV 226}}\n'''''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}''''' (The Spirit gives aid to our weakness), [[Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis|BWV]] 226, is a [[Motets (Bach)|motet]] by [[Johann Sebastian Bach]], composed in Leipzig in 1729 for the funeral of [[Johann Heinrich Ernesti]].\n\n== History ==\nFor ''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}'' <!-- as well as one other Bach motet{{explain|date=October 2015}} not needed Gerda Arendt 31 Nov 2015 -->, the [[autograph]] score survives. Bach himself noted on its title: \"{{lang|de|J. J. Motetta \u00e0 doi Cori bey Beerdigung des seel. Hrn. Prof. und Rectoris Ernesti di J. S. Bach}}.\" (''{{lang|la|[[Jesu Juva]]}}'' \u2013 Motet for two choirs for the funeral for the blessed [[Rector (academia)#Germany|Rector]], Professor Ernesti, by J. S. Bach). Ernesti was professor of poetry at [[Leipzig University]] and director of the [[Thomasschule]]. The first performance took place in the [[Paulinerkirche, Leipzig|Paulinerkirche]], the university church). Scholars debate if the performance was 24 October, or rather 21 October, as indicated by the title page of the sermon.<ref name=\"petzold\" />\n\nBach wrote a number of works for occasions of Leipzig University. Twelve such works survive: they are mainly festive in character (in German they have been categorised as ''Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern'').<ref name=\"Timm\">{{cite book | last = Timm | first = David | authorlink = David Timm | url = http://www.uni-leipzig.de/unichor/index.php?page=fe stmusiken | title = Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern | publisher = [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tschor]] | year = 2009 | pages = 8f | language = German | accessdate = 2 December 2012}}</ref> \nAs well as being part of a series of works connected with the university, ''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'' as a funeral motet is one of a series of Bach motets. \n\n=== Text ===\nThe text is taken from the [[Epistle to the Romans]] ({{Sourcetext|source=Bible|version=King James|book=Romans|chapter=8|verse=26|range=\u201327}}) and [[Martin Luther]]'s third stanza to the hymn \"{{lang|de|[[Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott]]}}\" (1524).<ref name=\"choralet\" /> Ernesti himself had chosen the text from the epistle for the funeral sermon.<ref name=\"klek\" />\n\n== Scoring and structure ==\n\nThe motet is structured in three movements and scored for two four-part choirs. They sing together in movements 2 and 3. The orchestral parts are extant, indicating that choir I was doubled by strings, choir II by reeds (two [[oboe]]s, [[Taille (instrument)|taille]] and [[bassoon]]). For the [[basso continuo]], separate [[violone]] and [[Organ (music)|organ]] parts are provided.<ref name=\"bachchoir\" />\n\n# ''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}''\n# ''{{lang|de|Der aber die Herzen forschet}}''\n# ''{{lang|de|Du heilige Brunst, s\u00fc\u00dfer Trost}}''\n\n== Music ==\n\nBach composed the text according to its meaning, not as music for mourning.<ref name=\"klek\" /> The opening contrasts two choirs in imitation. In lively 3/8 time, the word \"{{lang|de|Geist}}\" (Spirit) is illustrated by a lively [[melisma]]tic figure. The following idea, \"{{lang|de|Sondern der Geist selbst vertritt uns}}\" (but the Spirit itself intercedes for), is given as a [[fugue]], first with independent entrances of all eight parts, but concentrated to four parts in the end, \"{{lang|de|mit unaussprechlichem Seufzen}}\" (with unutterable sighs).<ref name=\"bachchoir\" /> The sighs are audible in the broken melodic lines of all voices.<ref name=\"arnold\" /> The thought \"{{lang|de|Der aber die Herzen forschet}}\" (He, however, who examines hearts) appears as a double fugue in four parts in {{lang|la|[[Prima pratica|stile antico]]}}.<ref name=\"bachchoir\" /> Here the word \"{{lang|de|Heiligen}}\" (saints) is illustrated in extended melismatic writing. The closing Pentecostal chorale<ref name=\"choralem\" /> is set for four parts.<ref name=\"arnold\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"petzold\">{{cite book\n| last = Petzoldt\n| first = Martin\n| authorlink = Martin Petzoldt\n| title = Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf BWV 226, in \"Booklet for the Anniversary Edition [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsmusik]], Johann Sebastian Bach: ''Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern.''\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"choralet\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Texts/Chorale103-Eng3.htm\n| title = Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott / Text and Translation of Chorale\n| publisher = bach-cantatas.com\n| year = 2006\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"timm\">{{cite book\n| last = Timm\n| first = David\n| authorlink = David Timm\n| url = http://www.uni-leipzig.de/unichor/index.php?page=festmusiken\n| title = Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern\n| publisher = [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tschor]]\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 22 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bachchoir\">{{cite book\n| last = Traupman-Carr\n| first = Carol\n| url = http://www.bach.org/bach101/motets/motet_dergeist_226.html\n| title = Motet BWV 226 \"Der Geist hilft\"\n| publisher = bach.org\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 22 October 2012\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130116230659/http://www.bach.org/bach101/motets/motet_dergeist_226.html\n| archive-date = 16 January 2013\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"arnold\">{{cite book\n| last = Arnold\n| first = Jochen\n| url = http://www.landeskirche-hannovers.de/evlka-de/presse-und-medien/frontnews/2012/09/09\n| title = Der Geist hilft unserer Schwachheit auf (BWV 226)\n| publisher = Landeskirche Hannover\n| date = 9 September 2012\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"klek\">{{cite book\n| last = Klek\n| first = Konrad\n| url = http://www.sonntagsblatt-bayern.de/news/aktuell/2012_18_17_01.htm\n| title = Von Schwachheit keine Spur / Serie Musica Sacra (60): Motette \"Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf\" von Johann Sebastian Bach\n| publisher = Sonntagsblatt Bayern\n| date = 29 April 2012\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202104410/http://www.sonntagsblatt-bayern.de/news/aktuell/2012_18_17_01.htm\n| archive-date = 2 February 2014\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"choralem\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.bach-cantatas.com/CM/Komm-Heiliger-Geist-Herre-Gott.htm\n| title = Chorale Melodies used in Bach's Vocal Works / Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott\n| publisher = bach-cantatas.com\n| year = 2006\n| accessdate = 28 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== Sources ==\n* {{IMSLP2|work=Der_Geist_hilft_unsrer_Schwachheit_auf,_BWV_226_%28Bach,_Johann_Sebastian%29|cname=Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf}}\n* [http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231.htm Motets BWV 225-231] history, scoring, sources for text and music, translations to various languages, discography, discussion, ''bach-cantatas'' website\n* [http://www.emmanuelmusic.org/notes_translations/translations_motets/t_bwv226.htm Bach Motet Translations / BWV 226 - \"Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf\"] English translation, discussion, [[Emmanuel Music]]\n* [http://www.bach.de/werk/bwv/226.html Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf] history, scoring, ''Bach'' website {{in lang|de}}\n* [http://www.uvm.edu/~classics/faculty/bach/BWV226.html BWV 226 Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf] English translation, [[University of Vermont]]\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [[Klaus Hofmann]]: ''Johann Sebastian Bach. Die Motetten''. B\u00e4renreiter, Kassel 2003, {{ISBN|3-7618-1499-2}}.\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://allofbach.com/en/bwv/bwv-226/ Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf, BWV 226]: performance by the [[Netherlands Bach Society]] (video and background information)\n* [http://www.klassika.info/Komponisten/Bach/Motette/BWV_0226/index.html Johann Sebastian Bach (1685\u20131750) / Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf] klassika.info {{in lang|de}}\n* Free MP3 recording of [http://www.acc.umu.se/~akadkor/cgi-bin/acc_download.cgi/3mp3/Der%20Geist%20hilft%204.mp3 Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf \u2013 BWV 226] from [http://www.acc.umu.se/~akadkor/indexENG.html Ume\u00e5 Akademiska K\u00f6r]\n\n{{Bach motets}}\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Geist Hilft Unsrer Schwachheit Auf, Der}}\n[[Category:Motets by Johann Sebastian Bach]]\n[[Category:Christian funeral music]]\n[[Category:1729 compositions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Motet by Johann Sebastian Bach}}\n{{Infobox Bach composition\n| title                 = {{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}\n| bwv                   = 226\n| type                  = [[Motet (Bach)|Motet]]\n| image                 = Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf.JPEG\n| image_upright         = 1.2\n| caption               = Manuscript\n| key                   = [[B-flat major]]\n| occasion              = Funeral of [[Johann Heinrich Ernesti]]\n| performed             = {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|1729|10|21|df=y}}|location=[[Paulinerkirche, Leipzig]]}}\n| bible                 = {{Sourcetext|source=Bible|version=King James|book=Romans|chapter=8|verse=26|range=\u201327}}\n| chorale               = [[Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott]]\n| movements             = 3\n| vocal                 = 2 choirs [[SATB|{{abbr|SATB|soprano, alto, tenor and bass}}]]\n| instrumental          = strings with choir I, woodwinds with choir II, continuo\n| italic title          = no\n}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', BWV 226}}\n'''''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}''''' (The Spirit gives aid to our weakness), [[Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis|BWV]] 226, is a [[Motets (Bach)|motet]] by [[Johann Sebastian Bach]], composed in Leipzig in 1729 for the funeral of [[Johann Heinrich Ernesti]].\n\n== History ==\nFor ''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}'' <!-- as well as one other Bach motet{{explain|date=October 2015}} not needed Gerda Arendt 31 Nov 2015 -->, the [[autograph]] score survives. Bach himself noted on its title: \"{{lang|de|J. J. Motetta \u00e0 doi Cori bey Beerdigung des seel. Hrn. Prof. und Rectoris Ernesti di J. S. Bach}}.\" (''{{lang|la|[[Jesu Juva]]}}'' \u2013 Motet for two choirs for the funeral for the blessed [[Rector (academia)#Germany|Rector]], Professor Ernesti, by J. S. Bach). Ernesti was professor of poetry at the University and director of the [[Thomasschule]]. The first performance took place in the [[Paulinerkirche, Leipzig|Paulinerkirche]], the university church). Scholars debate if the performance was 24 October, or rather 21 October, as indicated by the title page of the sermon.<ref name=\"petzold\" />\n\nBach wrote a number of works for occasions of [[Leipzig University]]. Twelve such works survive: they are mainly festive in character (in German they have been categorised as ''Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern'').<ref name=\"Timm\">{{cite book | last = Timm | first = David | authorlink = David Timm | url = http://www.uni-leipzig.de/unichor/index.php?page=fe stmusiken | title = Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern | publisher = [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tschor]] | year = 2009 | pages = 8f | language = German | accessdate = 2 December 2012}}</ref> \nAs well as being part of a series of works connected with the university, ''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'' as a funeral motet is one of a series of Bach motets. \n\n=== Text ===\nThe text is taken from the [[Epistle to the Romans]] ({{Sourcetext|source=Bible|version=King James|book=Romans|chapter=8|verse=26|range=\u201327}}) and [[Martin Luther]]'s third stanza to the hymn \"{{lang|de|[[Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott]]}}\" (1524).<ref name=\"choralet\" /> Ernesti himself had chosen the text from the epistle for the funeral sermon.<ref name=\"klek\" />\n\n== Scoring and structure ==\n\nThe motet is structured in three movements and scored for two four-part choirs. They sing together in movements 2 and 3. The orchestral parts are extant, indicating that choir I was doubled by strings, choir II by reeds (two [[oboe]]s, [[Taille (instrument)|taille]] and [[bassoon]]). For the [[basso continuo]], separate [[violone]] and [[Organ (music)|organ]] parts are provided.<ref name=\"bachchoir\" />\n\n# ''{{lang|de|Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf}}''\n# ''{{lang|de|Der aber die Herzen forschet}}''\n# ''{{lang|de|Du heilige Brunst, s\u00fc\u00dfer Trost}}''\n\n== Music ==\n\nBach composed the text according to its meaning, not as music for mourning.<ref name=\"klek\" /> The opening contrasts two choirs in imitation. In lively 3/8 time, the word \"{{lang|de|Geist}}\" (Spirit) is illustrated by a lively [[melisma]]tic figure. The following idea, \"{{lang|de|Sondern der Geist selbst vertritt uns}}\" (but the Spirit itself intercedes for), is given as a [[fugue]], first with independent entrances of all eight parts, but concentrated to four parts in the end, \"{{lang|de|mit unaussprechlichem Seufzen}}\" (with unutterable sighs).<ref name=\"bachchoir\" /> The sighs are audible in the broken melodic lines of all voices.<ref name=\"arnold\" /> The thought \"{{lang|de|Der aber die Herzen forschet}}\" (He, however, who examines hearts) appears as a double fugue in four parts in {{lang|la|[[Prima pratica|stile antico]]}}.<ref name=\"bachchoir\" /> Here the word \"{{lang|de|Heiligen}}\" (saints) is illustrated in extended melismatic writing. The closing Pentecostal chorale<ref name=\"choralem\" /> is set for four parts.<ref name=\"arnold\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"petzold\">{{cite book\n| last = Petzoldt\n| first = Martin\n| authorlink = Martin Petzoldt\n| title = Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf BWV 226, in \"Booklet for the Anniversary Edition [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsmusik]], Johann Sebastian Bach: ''Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern.''\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"choralet\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Texts/Chorale103-Eng3.htm\n| title = Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott / Text and Translation of Chorale\n| publisher = bach-cantatas.com\n| year = 2006\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"timm\">{{cite book\n| last = Timm\n| first = David\n| authorlink = David Timm\n| url = http://www.uni-leipzig.de/unichor/index.php?page=festmusiken\n| title = Festmusiken zu Leipziger Universit\u00e4tsfeiern\n| publisher = [[Leipziger Universit\u00e4tschor]]\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 22 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bachchoir\">{{cite book\n| last = Traupman-Carr\n| first = Carol\n| url = http://www.bach.org/bach101/motets/motet_dergeist_226.html\n| title = Motet BWV 226 \"Der Geist hilft\"\n| publisher = bach.org\n| year = 2009\n| pages = 8f\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 22 October 2012\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130116230659/http://www.bach.org/bach101/motets/motet_dergeist_226.html\n| archive-date = 16 January 2013\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"arnold\">{{cite book\n| last = Arnold\n| first = Jochen\n| url = http://www.landeskirche-hannovers.de/evlka-de/presse-und-medien/frontnews/2012/09/09\n| title = Der Geist hilft unserer Schwachheit auf (BWV 226)\n| publisher = Landeskirche Hannover\n| date = 9 September 2012\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"klek\">{{cite book\n| last = Klek\n| first = Konrad\n| url = http://www.sonntagsblatt-bayern.de/news/aktuell/2012_18_17_01.htm\n| title = Von Schwachheit keine Spur / Serie Musica Sacra (60): Motette \"Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf\" von Johann Sebastian Bach\n| publisher = Sonntagsblatt Bayern\n| date = 29 April 2012\n| language = German\n| accessdate = 25 October 2012\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202104410/http://www.sonntagsblatt-bayern.de/news/aktuell/2012_18_17_01.htm\n| archive-date = 2 February 2014\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"choralem\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.bach-cantatas.com/CM/Komm-Heiliger-Geist-Herre-Gott.htm\n| title = Chorale Melodies used in Bach's Vocal Works / Komm, Heiliger Geist, Herre Gott\n| publisher = bach-cantatas.com\n| year = 2006\n| accessdate = 28 October 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== Sources ==\n* {{IMSLP2|work=Der_Geist_hilft_unsrer_Schwachheit_auf,_BWV_226_%28Bach,_Johann_Sebastian%29|cname=Der Geist hilft unsrer Schwachheit auf}}\n* [http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231.htm Motets BWV 225-231] history, scoring, sources for text and music, translations to 